Synopsis:
Yash Raj Films’ Saiyaara is an intense love story, that launches Ahaan Panday and Aneet Padda as the next YRF hero and heroine respectively. 

Directed by Mohit Suri, a master of the romance genre, Saiyaara tells a pure-hearted love story of two youngsters Vaani and Krish. While Vaani writes, Krish sings and they both make music together. Though poles apart in their lives, beliefs and backgrounds, Vaani and Krish are perfect with each other and for each other. Will they understand that truth despite their age, their problems? 

They say flawed, imperfect people make for a perfect love story…and Saiyaara is about celebrating that one love story that is so deep, so pure and so caring that it is absolutely unconditional.

Vaani and Krish will have to navigate life, their problems, their insecurities to hopefully realise that only love can be the answer to everything. Saiyaara is a film that celebrates every season of love through the eyes of Vaani & Krish and poses a simple question…do you love someone so much that you would bet everything to keep that person in your life?

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. “Alpha”, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

snippet.title: সাঈদ আহমাদের সময়ের সেরা প্রতিবাদী গজল । পার পাবেনা। Sayed Ahmad Kalarab 2025
snippet.description:
সাঈদ আহমাদের সময়ের সেরা প্রতিবাদী গজল । পার পাবেনা। Sayed Ahmad Kalarab 2025

Artsit : Sayed Ahmad
Lyric : Yeasin Rubel
Tune : Sayed Ahmad
Sound Design : Abir Hasan 
GFX : Tawhid Jamil 
Video Director : Abdur Rahman Saifi
Management : Murshed Siraji
Online Support : HNS Digital
Naghma Records Presents 

#sayedahmadkalarab 
#প্রতিবাদীগজল
#kalarab 
#islamicsong 
#ghazal 

জাহেলিয়াত হার মেনে যায় 
দেখে ওদের নোংরামি 
চোখের সামনে মানুষ মেরে 
যাচ্ছে করে গুণ্ডামি 
বদ্ধ কারার রুদ্ধ দ্বারে 
করছে আঘাত হৃদপাঁজরে 
তপ্ত রাগের অগ্নিগীরি উঠছেযে শুধুই ফুঁসে।

দেশ কিনেছি একাত্তরে, দেশ কিনেছি চব্বিশে, 
দুর্নীতিবাজ সন্ত্রাসীরা পার পাবে না এই দেশে।।


বুকের ছাতি ঝাঁঝরা করে 
মুক্ত হলো এই ওতন 
আবার কারা হিংস্র হয়ে 
করছে এখন নির্যাতন?
মুগ্ধরা সব উঠলে জেগে 
পালিয়ে যাবে চতুর্দিকে 
আধারঘেরা ঘোর প্রলয়ের বৈরী মহাত্রাসে।।


ধর্ষিতা বোন থাকবে না আর 
হুমকি ভয়ে মুখ চেপে 
জ্বলবে অনল চতুর্দিকে
উঠবে মাটি ফের কেঁপে 
জালিম-শাহীর সিংহাসনে 
তীব্র ক্ষোভের অগ্নিবাণে 
মাতাল ঢেউয়ের লাল সাগরে হারিয়ে যাবে শেষে।।


চলবে না আর দখলবাজি 
থাকবে না তো চাঁদাবাজ 
ধরার বুকে কায়েম হলে 
ইসলামেরই শাসনরাজ 
আল-কুরআনের বিধান এলে 
শান্তি পাবে সবাই মিলে 
ক্ষমতার ঐ নোংরা খেলা চূর্ন হবে সবশেষে

snippet.description:
Saif Zohan Presents Bangla Original Song " Kichhu Manush More Jaay Pochishe". The Song's Lyrics written, Composed and Sung By Saif Zohan. The music is arranged by Shovon Roy. This song is a deeply emotional reflection on what it feels like to slowly lose yourself while still going through the motions of life. It speaks about how, for some, a part of them dies at 25 — their dreams, their spark — yet they keep living, pretending, surviving. Through powerful and poetic lines, it captures the quiet heartbreak of growing up, forgetting childhood dreams, and hiding behind masks just to fit in. It’s a song about feeling alone in a crowd, questioning your worth, and wondering when — or if — you’ll ever feel truly alive again.

snippet.title: Bangladesh Jet Crash How it Happened?
snippet.description:
The Bangladesh jet crash occurred on July 21st, 2025, when a Bangladesh Air Force F-7  BGI fighter jet crashed into Milestone School & College in Dhaka's Uttara area shortly after takeoff from Kurmitola airbase during a routine training flight.

At around 1:06 PM local time, a Bangladesh Air Force F-7 BGI training jet lifted off from BAF Base Bir Uttom A.K. Khand ker in Dhaka.

At the controls was Flight Lieutenant Toukir Islam Sagar, embarking on what was meant to be his first solo fighter mission.

It was a routine training flight—one of many that take place regularly in the skies over the capital.

But only moments after takeoff, something went wrong. A technical malfunction struck the aircraft, causing it to stall and become unresponsive.

From the control tower came a swift command for the pilot to eject, but the plane was already flying too low. 

There simply wasn’t enough altitude for a safe ejection.

Fully aware of the danger, Flight Lieutenant Sagar fought to regain control.
He tried to steer the stricken jet away from populated areas, aiming for open ground. But time and altitude were against him.

Sometime between 1:10 and 1:15 PM, the aircraft crashed near the main gate of Milestone School & College in the Uttara area of Dhaka.

It struck the side of a two-story building while classes were still underway. Hundreds of students were inside at the time.

snippet.title: Bare Bare Aar Asha Hobe Na | Fakira (Unplugged) | Bengali Folk Music
snippet.description:
🎵 Bare Bare Aar Asha Hobena "Unplugged" | BHOBA PAGLA | FAKIRA | Bengali Folk Song 2025

"এমন মানব জনম আর পাবে না, বারে বারে আর আসা হবে না..."

A timeless message echoes through this haunting Bengali folk song — life is fleeting, and every moment is sacred. "Bare Bare Aar Asha Hobena" is written and composed by Bhoba Pagla, whose words urge the soul to awaken before it's too late.

Performed by FAKIRA, the song merges mystical lyrics with rooted folk instrumentation, invoking a deep reflection on life, karma, and time.

Let this song remind you that the human birth is rare, and we must live it with awareness — because we won’t come back again and again.
